     <h2><font color="#000080"><!-- 2004-09-02 -->
	 
	 What's Not To Love About Seattle?
	 </font>
     </h2>
    

	<p>
    <div style="clear:both;"></div><p align="center">&nbsp;{tags: <a href="http://www.technorati.com/tag/orcmid" rel="tag">orcmid</a> <a href="http://www.technorati.com/tag/Seattle" rel="tag">Seattle</a> <a href="http://www.technorati.com/tag/Seattle" rel="tag">Metro</a> <a href="http://www.technorati.com/tag/transit+advertisement" rel="tag">transit advertisement</a> <a href="http://www.technorati.com/tag/jobs" rel="tag">jobs</a> <a href="http://www.technorati.com/tag/Mariners" rel="tag">Mariners</a>}</p><blockquote><p><font face="Arial" color="#808080">YOUR AMAZING NEW JOB is managed so efficiently you find time to volunteer at a local animal shelter where you bond with a Shi Tzu named Miss Tinkles who has canine leukemia and begin inadvertently treating her through positive energy therapy which miraculously cures her and the CDC mass produces the treatment and completely eradicates cancer and the rain stops and 37 rainbows appear over the Space Needle and their refraction power is harnessed as an unlimited fuel source and a certain Yankee comes back to the Mariners for free and takes all the money he&rsquo;s earned since he left and divides it equally among all the people IN SEATTLE.</font></p></blockquote><p align="right"><a href="http://nwjobs.com/">nwjobs.com</a> you matter.</p><hr><p>Now that transit art has moved to the exterior of the bus, there needs to be something else to catch the rider&rsquo;s eye.&nbsp; Seattle Metro has been putting up urban poetry for the riders.&nbsp; Topping that, I saw&nbsp;this creative&nbsp;transit advertisement&nbsp;above the windows&nbsp;across from me as I traversed Lake Washington last night.&nbsp; After reading it several times, I pulled out my notebook and copied the text before&nbsp;arriving at my transfer point and the remaining ride home.&nbsp; Although I don&rsquo;t have ads on this blog, I figure NWjobs deserves the link love for providing such a provocative invitation.</p><div style="clear:both; padding-bottom: 0.25em;"></div>
    </p>
	<span class="byline">posted by orcmid 
       at <a href="http://orcmid.com/blog/2007/01/whats-not-to-love-about-seattle.asp">1/19/2007 09:43:28 AM</a></span>
	  
